focus and concentration

160
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:11,100
and how they are created

161
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:14,070
by the various chemical
systems within your brain.

162
00:06:14,070 --> 00:06:16,110
We're going to hear a lot about
these chemical systems again

163
00:06:16,110 --> 00:06:19,440
today in the context of nicotine
and they are as follows.

164
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,970
You can think about focus

165
00:06:20,970 --> 00:06:24,000
on any goal or any endeavor as an arrow.

166
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,130
So just imagine an arrow
which has an arrow head

167
00:06:26,130 --> 00:06:27,810
and a shaft, and we'll
add a third component

168
00:06:27,810 --> 00:06:28,713
to it in a moment.

169
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,170
The head of the arrow,

170
00:06:31,170 --> 00:06:32,700
meaning the direction of your focus,

171
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:35,190
is largely set by acetylcholine,

172
00:06:35,190 --> 00:06:36,690
which is a chemical in the brain.

173
00:06:36,690 --> 00:06:39,780
The shaft of the arrow
is set by a chemical

174
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:42,600
called adrenaline, also
called epinephrine.

175
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,470
Those are the same thing.

176
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:46,260
In the brain typically it's
referred to as epinephrine,

177
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:47,280
and in the body,

178
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:49,140
it's more commonly
referred to as adrenaline,

179
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:51,060
but those are the same neurochemical.

180
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:54,300
Epinephrine slash adrenaline
represents the shaft

181
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:57,510
of the arrow and it's providing the energy

182
00:06:57,510 --> 00:06:59,220
for which to focus.

183
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:00,600
And then we can put behind that arrow

184
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,150
a little propeller or
a motor, if you like,

185
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:04,950
and the propeller or motor in the context

186
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:07,470
of this neurochemistry model is dopamine,

187
00:07:07,470 --> 00:07:09,180
which provides ongoing motivation.

188
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:11,670
It pushes that arrow forward continually

189
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:15,180
as you strive to focus
on a particular thing.

190
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:16,740
This particular arrow model,

191
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:19,680
that is your ability
to increase your focus,

192
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:23,070
can be enhanced therefore
by increasing acetylcholine,

193
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:26,700
epinephrine, and dopamine simultaneously.

194
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,410
And there are a lot of
different ways to do that.

195
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:29,910
But one of the more effective ways to do

196
00:07:29,910 --> 00:07:34,200
