01:31:09,803 --> 01:31:13,380
the negative health effects
that younger people are smoking,

2250
01:31:13,380 --> 01:31:14,970
that women are smoking more nowadays.

2251
01:31:14,970 --> 01:31:16,410
And that even though you see less smoking,

2252
01:31:16,410 --> 01:31:19,140
typically in the US and Canada,
and even in Northern Europe,

2253
01:31:19,140 --> 01:31:21,450
some places, there are still
many many people are smoking

2254
01:31:21,450 --> 01:31:24,840
who would like to quit,
but that 75% of people,

2255
01:31:24,840 --> 01:31:27,030
at least according to this
review earlier, I said 70%,

2256
01:31:27,030 --> 01:31:30,180
but estimates are as high as
75% of people who try to quit

2257
01:31:30,180 --> 01:31:32,760
smoking relapse within the first week.

2258
01:31:32,760 --> 01:31:34,290
The first week, they
just go right back to it.

2259
01:31:34,290 --> 01:31:36,810
That's how powerfully
reinforcing the nicotine is.

2260
01:31:36,810 --> 01:31:38,880
Remember, it's the nicotine
in the cigarette that's

2261
01:31:38,880 --> 01:31:43,880
powerfully reinforcing, but
it's also the oral habit,

2262
01:31:44,010 --> 01:31:45,360
the motor habit.

2263
01:31:45,360 --> 01:31:46,830
There is this thing about density

2264
01:31:46,830 --> 01:31:48,240
of sensory receptors in the lips.

2265
01:31:48,240 --> 01:31:50,613
People like bringing things to their lips,

2266
01:31:51,480 --> 01:31:56,480
food, cigarettes, other lips
in some cases, et cetera,

2267
01:31:56,610 --> 01:31:59,010
there is a reinforcement
pathway related to that

2268
01:31:59,010 --> 01:32:01,470
for sort of obvious adaptive reasons.

2269
01:32:01,470 --> 01:32:05,490
And as a consequence,
there is a reinforcement,

2270
01:32:05,490 --> 01:32:07,590
both from the behavior
and from the dopamine

2271
01:32:07,590 --> 01:32:09,180
released from the nicotine itself.

2272
01:32:09,180 --> 01:32:10,560
And as I mentioned earlier,

2273
01:32:10,560 --> 01:32:12,720
from the positive reinforcement

2274
01:32:12,720 --> 01:32:13,950
that comes from increased focus.

2275
01:32:13,950 --> 01:32:15,300
So the money that you make through work

2276
01:32:15,300 --> 01:32:16,680
or your attentional ability

2277
01:32:16,680 --> 01:32:18,630
or the fact that you're alert
and people feel you present,

2278
01:32:18,630 --> 01:32:21,900
all of that funnels back
into positive reinforcement,

2279
01:32:21,900 --> 01:32:23,790
behavioral reinforcement,

2280
01:32:23,790 --> 01:32:26,280
and then what we would call addiction.

2281
01:32:26,280 --> 01:32:30,240
So this review covers all of
that and then steps beautifully

2282
01:32:30,240 --> 01:32:33,840
through nicotine replacement
therapy and various compounds,

2283
01:32:33,840 --> 01:32:35,760
several of which I'm
going to talk about now,

2284
01:32:35,760 --> 01:32:38,430
which have been shown to increase
that number that we talked

2285
01:32:38,430 --> 01:32:41,490
about earlier of only 5%
of people who try to quit

2286
01:32:41,490 --> 01:32:44,430
with no other support
pharmacologic or hypnosis

2287
01:32:44,430 --> 01:32:47,070
or otherwise just say that's it,
I'm not going to smoke again,

2288
01:32:47,070 --> 01:32:48,690
or I'm not going to vape again,

2289
01:32:48,690 --> 01:32:50,940
only 5% of people succeed in doing that.

2290
01:32:50,940 --> 01:32:53,790
And even among those, many
end up relapsing later,

2291
01:32:53,790 --> 01:32:55,890
there are a couple
pharmacologic approaches.

2292
01:32:55,890 --> 01:32:57,930
One of the main ones that's
received a lot of attention in

2293
01:32:57,930 --> 01:32:59,230
recent years is Bupropion,

2294
01:33:00,120 --> 01:33:04,110
sometimes referred to by its
commercial name Wellbutrin.

2295
01:33:04,110 --> 01:33:09,110
Now Bupropion is a compound
that increases the release of

2296
01:33:09,270 --> 01:33:11,940
dopamine and to a lesser
extent epinephrine

2297
01:33:11,940 --> 01:33:13,620
and some other neurochemicals as well.

2298
01:33:13,620 --> 01:33:15,660
It's used for the treatment of depression

2299
01:33:15,660 --> 01:33:17,730
and for smoking cessation.

2300
01:33:17,730 --> 01:33:19,980
Now I want to point out
again, I'm not a psychiatrist,

2301
01:33:19,980 --> 01:33:23,490
so I'm not telling you to take
Bupropion, AKA Wellbutrin,

2302
01:33:23,490 --> 01:33:25,500
but I'm going to give you a little
bit of the contour of what's

2303
01:33:25,500 --> 01:33:28,500
typically done in terms of
Bupropion administration

2304
01:33:28,500 --> 01:33:31,410
to help people get relief
from some of the withdrawal

2305
01:33:31,410 --> 01:33:33,930
symptoms of trying to
quit smoking or vaping

2306
01:33:33,930 --> 01:33:36,570
or other forms of nicotine ingestion.

2307
01:33:36,570 --> 01:33:41,010
Typically Bupropion is taken
in 300 milligram per day

2308
01:33:41,010 --> 01:33:44,190
doses divided into two dosages
of 150 milligrams each,

2309
01:33:44,190 --> 01:33:47,250
or sometimes there's a
slow release formula.

2310
01:33:47,250 --> 01:33:49,950
The dosages will vary
from person to person.

2311
01:33:49,950 --> 01:33:51,980
I want to really emphasize that there

2312
01:33:51,980 --> 01:33:54,690
is an increased seizure
risk with Bupropion.

2313
01:33:54,690 --> 01:33:56,970
It only occurs in a small
fraction of the population,

2314
01:33:56,970 --> 01:33:58,980
but nonetheless is a real concern

2315
01:33:58,980 --> 01:34:00,420
for those members of the population.

2316
01:34:00,420 --> 01:34:02,220
So for those of you with seizure risk,

2317
01:34:02,220 --> 01:34:03,660
whether you know it or not,

2318
01:34:03,660 --> 01:34:06,180
that's going to be a valid concern

2319
01:34:06,180 --> 01:34:08,010
in terms of potential side effects.

2320
01:34:08,010 --> 01:34:11,760
The other thing about Bupropion
is that it has to be used

2321
01:34:11,760 --> 01:34:14,160
with caution in patients that
have liver disease or renal

2322
01:34:14,160 --> 01:34:16,620
disease that can impact the amount

2323
01:34:16,620 --> 01:34:18,720
that anyone can take meaning
sometimes people have to take

2324
01:34:18,720 --> 01:34:20,790
a much lower dose if
they have renal disease

2325
01:34:20,790 --> 01:34:22,230
or liver disease.

2326
01:34:22,230 --> 01:34:23,940
And sometimes they can't take it at all.

2327
01:34:23,940 --> 01:34:26,670
Sometimes if people are taking
benzodiazepines for whatever

2328
01:34:26,670 --> 01:34:28,143
reason or other sedatives,

2329
01:34:28,994 --> 01:34:32,169
there are contraindications
there, so Bupropion isn't a

2330
01:34:32,169 --> 01:34:34,380
kind of one size fits all or magic bullet

2331
01:34:34,380 --> 01:34:36,420
for quitting smoking, nonetheless,

2332
01:34:36,420 --> 01:34:38,070
for people that can take it safely,

2333
01:34:38,070 --> 01:34:39,900
and again, this is a prescription drug,

2334
01:34:39,900 --> 01:34:42,510
a board certified psychiatrist
or other physician is going

2335
01:34:42,510 --> 01:34:44,640
to have to prescribe it for you
if it's appropriate for you.

2336
01:34:44,640 --> 01:34:48,240
And it moves that number of
5% success rate to about what

2337
01:34:48,240 --> 01:34:53,240
one sees with the clinical
hypnosis to about 20% of people

2338
01:34:53,370 --> 01:34:56,790
will successfully overcome their nicotine,

2339
01:34:56,790 --> 01:35:00,300
or I should say their
smoking or vaping addiction.

2340
01:35:00,300 --> 01:35:03,540
Now it's important to ask
why this would work, right?

2341
01:35:03,540 --> 01:35:08,250
It's not as if Bupropion is
increasing nicotine per se.

2342
01:35:08,250 --> 01:35:09,600
What it's doing is it's tapping

2343
01:35:09,600 --> 01:35:12,330
on that mesolimbic reward
pathway, increasing dopamine,

2344
01:35:12,330 --> 01:35:15,180
or at least allowing dopamine
levels to say substantially

2345
01:35:15,180 --> 01:35:18,990
elevated enough that people
don't experience some of the

2346
01:35:18,990 --> 01:35:21,420
drop in dopamine that leads
to the withdrawal symptoms,

2347
01:35:21,420 --> 01:35:22,860
the lessening of mood, et cetera.

2348
01:35:22,860 --> 01:35:24,660
And it's no coincidence that Bupropion

2349
01:35:24,660 --> 01:35:26,430
is also an antidepressant.

2350
01:35:26,430 --> 01:35:28,950
It's a common antidepressant
for people that experience

2351
01:35:28,950 --> 01:35:31,290
negative side effects
with the so-called SSRIs,

2352
01:35:31,290 --> 01:35:34,500
the selective serotonin
reuptake inhibitors that prevent

2353
01:35:34,500 --> 01:35:36,510
them from taking those
things like lessen libido

2354
01:35:36,510 --> 01:35:37,343
or appetite,

2355
01:35:37,343 --> 01:35:39,900
or in some cases increased
appetite or any number

2356
01:35:39,900 --> 01:35:42,060
of other side effects
that some people, not all,

2357
01:35:42,060 --> 01:35:43,830
but some people experience with SSRIs.

2358
01:35:43,830 --> 01:35:45,270
They'll be prescribed Wellbutrin,

2359
01:35:45,270 --> 01:35:48,180
Bupropion is the generic name.

2360
01:35:48,180 --> 01:35:50,190
So Wellbutrin being the
commercial name again,

2361
01:35:50,190 --> 01:35:54,510
Bupropion is what they'll be
prescribed instead with the

2362
01:35:54,510 --> 01:35:57,600
caveats of seizure risk, renal disease,

2363
01:35:57,600 --> 01:35:58,923
liver disease, et cetera.

2364
01:35:59,760 --> 01:36:02,460
The outcomes with Wellbutrin
for smoking cessation

2365
01:36:02,460 --> 01:36:04,020
are pretty good if you
think about an increase

2366
01:36:04,020 --> 01:36:07,110
from 5% to 20%, that's pretty dramatic.

2367
01:36:07,110 --> 01:36:10,380
And yet I also want to refer
back to the incredible success

2368
01:36:10,380 --> 01:36:12,120
of the clinical hypnosis approach.

2369
01:36:12,120 --> 01:36:14,730
Again, you can find that at reveri.com,

2370
01:36:14,730 --> 01:36:19,163
the clinical hypnosis approach
has a success rate of 23%.

2371
01:36:20,126 --> 01:36:20,959
So it's very closely aligned with,

2372
01:36:20,959 --> 01:36:24,420
if not exceeding the
success rate with Bupropion.

2373
01:36:24,420 --> 01:36:26,580
Of course there are other
pharmacologic approaches

2374
01:36:26,580 --> 01:36:29,610
to quitting smoking or vaping.

2375
01:36:29,610 --> 01:36:33,060
All of them generally circle
back to increasing dopamine

2376
01:36:33,060 --> 01:36:35,250
and/or norepinephrine in order to offset

2377
01:36:35,250 --> 01:36:38,460
some of the withdrawal
symptoms of smoking cessation

2378
01:36:38,460 --> 01:36:39,720
or vaping cessation.

2379
01:36:39,720 --> 01:36:42,900
A very common approach for
people to try and quit smoking or

2380
01:36:42,900 --> 01:36:47,900
vaping is to use nicotine
itself to try and prevent people

2381
01:36:48,450 --> 01:36:52,290
from seeking nicotine through
a cigarette or a vape pen.

2382
01:36:52,290 --> 01:36:55,440
What I mean by that is people
using a nicotine patch or

2383
01:36:55,440 --> 01:36:59,070
nicotine gum or other
nicotine delivery device

2384
01:36:59,070 --> 01:37:02,010
that is not cigarettes and not vaping

2385
01:37:02,010 --> 01:37:05,250
in order to maintain levels of nicotine

2386
01:37:05,250 --> 01:37:07,110
in their bloodstream,

2387
01:37:07,110 --> 01:37:09,510
which of course means maintain
levels of nicotine in their

2388
01:37:09,510 --> 01:37:12,180
brain and body to the same extent

2389
01:37:12,180 --> 01:37:15,030
that they would if they
were smoking or vaping,

2390
01:37:15,030 --> 01:37:18,570
maybe even gradually taking
down the total amount of

2391
01:37:18,570 --> 01:37:21,630
nicotine in their brain
and body by reducing

2392
01:37:21,630 --> 01:37:24,960
the number or size of nicotine gum pieces

2393
01:37:24,960 --> 01:37:26,430
that they ingest each day,

2394
01:37:26,430 --> 01:37:29,040
or keeping the patch on for
a shorter amount of time

2395
01:37:29,040 --> 01:37:31,770
or getting a lower dose patch
that releases less nicotine

2396
01:37:31,770 --> 01:37:34,353
total or over time.

2397
01:37:35,490 --> 01:37:37,230
All of those approaches have been shown

2398
01:37:37,230 --> 01:37:39,120
to be reasonably successful,

2399
01:37:39,120 --> 01:37:40,230
I'll get to the numbers in a few minutes,

2400
01:37:40,230 --> 01:37:43,350
but reasonably successful
in allowing people

2401
01:37:43,350 --> 01:37:46,750
to quit smoking or vaping.

2402
01:37:46,750 --> 01:37:49,770
Again, most of the data
is on cigarette smoking

2403
01:37:49,770 --> 01:37:52,230
because vaping is a
relatively new phenomenon.

2404
01:37:52,230 --> 01:37:54,480
Although quite troublingly,

2405
01:37:54,480 --> 01:37:57,810
it's a very rapidly increasing behavior,

2406
01:37:57,810 --> 01:37:59,340
especially in the young population.

2407
01:37:59,340 --> 01:38:01,470
So that's why I'm kind of
lumping these two things together

2408
01:38:01,470 --> 01:38:06,210
because I think very soon we
are going to need an all out

2409
01:38:06,210 --> 01:38:09,600
campaign for how to
counter vaping addiction.

2410
01:38:09,600 --> 01:38:11,940
So what do we know about smoking cessation

2411
01:38:11,940 --> 01:38:13,560
using nicotine itself?

2412
01:38:13,560 --> 01:38:16,530
Is the patch best? Is nicotine gum best?

2413
01:38:16,530 --> 01:38:19,680
Turns out that a combination of approaches

2414
01:38:19,680 --> 01:38:21,660
is best, so somewhat surprising,

2415
01:38:21,660 --> 01:38:23,490
but it was very clear from the
literature that I was able to

2416
01:38:23,490 --> 01:38:27,390
find that using nicotine
patches for some period of time

2417
01:38:27,390 --> 01:38:29,250
and then switching to a gum

2418
01:38:29,250 --> 01:38:33,150
and then perhaps switching
to a nasal spray,

2419
01:38:33,150 --> 01:38:34,980
that's going to be the most effective.

2420
01:38:34,980 --> 01:38:38,130
Then the question is how long
to continue each of those

2421
01:38:38,130 --> 01:38:39,600
and whether or not to overlap them.

2422
01:38:39,600 --> 01:38:42,600
It seems as if doing one for
about a week and then switching

2423
01:38:42,600 --> 01:38:45,330
to another for about a week and
then switching to another is

2424
01:38:45,330 --> 01:38:47,820
one rationable and reasonable approach

2425
01:38:47,820 --> 01:38:50,190
that many people have used successfully.

2426
01:38:50,190 --> 01:38:51,090
Why would that be?

2427
01:38:51,090 --> 01:38:53,880
It all has to do with the
different rates of absorption

2428
01:38:53,880 --> 01:38:55,530
of nicotine into the bloodstream,

2429
01:38:55,530 --> 01:38:57,150
and then the downstream consequences

2430
01:38:57,150 --> 01:39:00,480
of that on the dopamine,
acetylcholine, epinephrine,

2431
01:39:00,480 --> 01:39:02,640
and other systems of the brain and body.

2432
01:39:02,640 --> 01:39:05,970
And while there hasn't been
an extremely detailed study

2433
01:39:05,970 --> 01:39:07,860
of the exact kinetics of

2434
01:39:07,860 --> 01:39:10,260
how the nasal sprays versus
the transdermal patches

2435
01:39:10,260 --> 01:39:12,090
versus the gums, et cetera, work,

2436
01:39:12,090 --> 01:39:13,560
there's a logical structure to it

2437
01:39:13,560 --> 01:39:14,880
that will immediately make sense to you.

2438
01:39:14,880 --> 01:39:16,323
First of all,

2439
01:39:16,323 --> 01:39:18,930
the transdermal patches
provide a fairly steady state

2440
01:39:18,930 --> 01:39:21,450
dopamine release across the day.

2441
01:39:21,450 --> 01:39:23,790
And oftentimes people are
wearing them at night as well.

2442
01:39:23,790 --> 01:39:26,850
This is relevant because if
people are ingesting nicotine

2443
01:39:26,850 --> 01:39:29,313
by way of smoking and vaping,

2444
01:39:30,360 --> 01:39:31,950
hopefully they're not waking
up in the middle of the night

2445
01:39:31,950 --> 01:39:32,910
just to smoke or vape.

2446
01:39:32,910 --> 01:39:34,200
Believe or not, some people do that,

2447
01:39:34,200 --> 01:39:36,390
but of course, while people are asleep,

2448
01:39:36,390 --> 01:39:38,550
they are not smoking or vaping.

2449
01:39:38,550 --> 01:39:39,480
They always tell you don't fall asleep

2450
01:39:39,480 --> 01:39:40,313
with a cigarette in your mouth,

2451
01:39:40,313 --> 01:39:42,330
you'll burn the whole house down,

2452
01:39:42,330 --> 01:39:45,510
but exceedingly rare to have people

2453
01:39:45,510 --> 01:39:47,040
are smoking in their sleep.

2454
01:39:47,040 --> 01:39:50,100
So people wake up in the morning
and because the half life

2455
01:39:50,100 --> 01:39:52,110
of nicotine from smoking
or vaping is very short,

2456
01:39:52,110 --> 01:39:54,030
anywhere from one to two hours,

2457
01:39:54,030 --> 01:39:55,980
they're essentially in a state
of withdrawal at the point

2458
01:39:55,980 --> 01:39:57,030
where they wake up in the morning.

2459
01:39:57,030 --> 01:39:57,900
How can I say that?

2460
01:39:57,900 --> 01:40:01,320
Remember, withdrawal sets in
about four hours after the last

2461
01:40:01,320 --> 01:40:03,210
ingestion of nicotine by cigarette

2462
01:40:03,210 --> 01:40:05,100
or by inhalation from the vape pen.

2463
01:40:05,100 --> 01:40:08,100
So people are waking up in
nicotine withdrawal and then

2464
01:40:08,100 --> 01:40:10,950
immediately going into the
behavior of ingesting nicotine,

2465
01:40:10,950 --> 01:40:13,620
or very soon after waking for most people.

2466
01:40:13,620 --> 01:40:15,660
So nicotine patch is going to be

2467
01:40:15,660 --> 01:40:17,910
very effective for a week or so, again,

2468
01:40:17,910 --> 01:40:20,520
talk to your physician about
the best approach for this,

2469
01:40:20,520 --> 01:40:23,940
but then switching to a nasal spray

2470
01:40:23,940 --> 01:40:26,160
or switching to nicotine
gum for about a week,

2471
01:40:26,160 --> 01:40:28,530
which is going to change the
kinetics of that nicotine

2472
01:40:28,530 --> 01:40:31,590
absorption into the bloodstream
and change the release

2473
01:40:31,590 --> 01:40:33,810
of dopamine and other
neurochemicals within the brain.

2474
01:40:33,810 --> 01:40:37,230
That's going to keep the system
intentionally off balance

2475
01:40:37,230 --> 01:40:40,890
so that it never comes to
expect one single pattern

2476
01:40:40,890 --> 01:40:44,040
or amplitude of dopamine release.

2477
01:40:44,040 --> 01:40:47,673
And that is a very powerful way for a,

2478
01:40:48,570 --> 01:40:51,750
let's just call it a
quitting method to work.

2479
01:40:51,750 --> 01:40:53,370
Because as I've always said,

2480
01:40:53,370 --> 01:40:56,280
the most powerful schedule of dopamine

2481
01:40:56,280 --> 01:40:59,190
is going to be this random
intermittent reward.

2482
01:40:59,190 --> 01:41:00,900
This is what's used in the casinos

2483
01:41:00,900 --> 01:41:02,100
in order to take your money.

2484
01:41:02,100 --> 01:41:03,780
And generally they do, on average,

2485
01:41:03,780 --> 01:41:06,360
they take your money more
than you take theirs,

2486
01:41:06,360 --> 01:41:08,100
and they take more of it.

2487
01:41:08,100 --> 01:41:09,660
Not just more often because

2488
01:41:09,660 --> 01:41:11,850
they use this random
intermittent schedule.

2489
01:41:11,850 --> 01:41:14,190
The random intermittent schedule
is one in which you don't

2490
01:41:14,190 --> 01:41:17,340
really know when the peaks in
dopamine are going to arrive.

2491
01:41:17,340 --> 01:41:19,830
And so there isn't this
expectation and craving.

2492
01:41:19,830 --> 01:41:21,510
And then all of a sudden
